Tell HN: Taipei HN Meetup – Wed 30th November
text:
Hi HN! We will organize our 2nd HN meetup Wednesday 30th November [1].

It could be awesome to meet HN folks who are in Taipei! The event link is https://www.eventbrite.com/e/taipei-hackernews-meetup-2-with-asianometry-tickets-468408070147

This time, Asianometry[1] will give a 10mn talk on how he reached 370k subscribers and US$5,000+/month all by himself. Asianometry makes in-depth videos and essays about semiconductors, tech, economics and history related to Taiwan. Several articles have been featured on HackerNews.

[1] https://www.youtube.com/c/asianometry

Suspended from Twitter and Facebook
text:
My startup's Twitter and Facebook accounts were suspended.

I created a Twitter account for my startup 2-weeks before Twitter's acquisition. I only ever edited the account's name and bio.

As of a few days ago: The account is now in limbo and says, "your account is suspended and not able to perform this action" when refreshing the page or trying to tweet or edit settings.

And, If that wasn't enough of a headache.

My startup company's Facebook account was also "permanently suspended" shortly after creating a Facebook Business Ad Account. I don't have a personal Facebook, so I was required to create one; I did so using my company email and then made a Business Ad Account off of that.

I was able to lift the suspension on my personal account by uploading a photocopy of my ID. However, the suspension on the company's Facebook account is still active. Automated emails from Facebook say to expect a response in 48 hours, but I have been waiting to hear back for a week.

And, if that wasn't enough of a headache.

I have a signed agreement with the local news to advertise my company/product towards the end of November.

This is a disaster.
